A real-world example of thread starvation is when a microservice uses a fixed thread pool and all threads get blocked waiting for slow downstream services like payment or database calls. New requests cannot get 
a thread and may wait indefinitely, leading to high latency or timeouts. This happens even if CPU is idle, making it tricky to diagnose. It can be mitigated using timeouts, circuit breakers, non-blocking I/O, or
proper thread pool design.

